00:34:11,048 --> 00:34:12,009
[SPEAKER_05]: the Haiti flag day.

422
00:34:12,951 --> 00:34:24,465
[SPEAKER_05]: And I looked it up and I learned about what their slogan, what they say to their flag, L'Union fait la force, is their motto.

423
00:34:24,605 --> 00:34:28,931
[SPEAKER_05]: And Haiti is called Haiti, so it's called the Rappo Haiti flag of Haiti.

424
00:34:30,092 --> 00:34:37,414
[SPEAKER_05]: O Haiti, beloved land of Taino and African, land of hills so green and tall, of you I sing a song for all.

425
00:34:38,074 --> 00:34:44,775
[SPEAKER_05]: O Haiti, O Haiti, O land of pain and sorrow, and joy and power and rage and blood and hopes for new tomorrows.

426
00:34:45,396 --> 00:34:53,197
[SPEAKER_05]: I salute you and embrace your flag that emerged in triumph after war, the upward march to claim your fate, sing l'union fait la force.

427
00:34:53,938 --> 00:34:59,739
[SPEAKER_05]: I see you and salute you for the land you wish to be, embrace you and I honor you and pray for harmony.

428
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:07,102
[SPEAKER_05]: O Haiti, O Haiti, O land of mountain stall, Land of struggle, land of beauty, I sing your rise and fall.

429
00:35:07,762 --> 00:35:14,424
[SPEAKER_05]: I see you and salute you, and I sing the song of you, Of those who fought to take back that which belongs to you.

430
00:35:15,084 --> 00:35:19,106
[SPEAKER_05]: In fateful 1791, O Haiti, you raised your head, And in the year 1804, you claimed your land and led.

431
00:35:22,847 --> 00:35:29,112
[SPEAKER_05]: I see you, I salute you, and I sing about your own, Of Toussaint, the all-saintly, who led the way alone.

432
00:35:29,132 --> 00:35:35,496
[SPEAKER_05]: I see you, and I sing about the man who led the way, L'ouverture, the opening, brought in the light of day.

433
00:35:36,057 --> 00:35:42,622
[SPEAKER_05]: And Toussaint was betrayed by one who did not keep his word, He died in France and never saw the dream which had occurred.

434
00:35:43,122 --> 00:35:50,548
[SPEAKER_05]: Your own flag flew, the white torn out, the red remained with blue, With the palm above the mountain, the year your story grew.

435
00:35:51,465 --> 00:35:58,210
[SPEAKER_05]: You hold your head up, buoyed by the hopes of one another, to live, to work, to eat, to dream a land where none are other.

436
00:35:58,230 --> 00:36:05,535
[SPEAKER_05]: O Haiti, O Haiti, O land of pain and sorrow, and joy and power and pride and blood and hopes for new tomorrows.

